race.comment: BAY OF THE SOUTH (6) has led for the judge at both of her runs to date but found a couple better on each occasion. Beautifully drawn and is nicely placed dropping back in trip. Will give them something to catch. SNITZSTREAM (11) returned from a spell and looked a different horse last time out, leading for home and giving a kick only to find the winner too strong close to the line in a 1000m Sunshine Coast maiden. Big chance to go one better. CERETTI (10) worked home well for third but was never a threat when fresh from a spell over this trip at the Gold Coast recently. Worth noting Angela Jones rides this one in preference to other Gollan runners. Right in the mix. HANSAGLORY (3) is a Hanseatic three-year-old on debut. Looks ready to go after filling a placing in a recent Doomben trial. First starter OVER SPRAY (4) won a Doomben trial on 15 December and has been kept away from the public since. Keep a close eye on the betting.
